{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/Powerline/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Learn to talk to computers","author":"nightwarriorftw"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"12aa7c46-c7b7-58e8-b451-440dd13fc012","excerpt":"This is how your current terminal looks like \n Now with some awesome tricks you can change it too\n Step 1 Install  and .\nFor Debian based operating system useâ€¦","html":"<p>This is how your current terminal looks like\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/895ab6686d4a312c27ffff0f702e3644/70c4b/terminal-without-powerline.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 80.24502297090352%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"terminal_without_powerline\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/895ab6686d4a312c27ffff0f702e3644/b9e4f/terminal-without-powerline.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/895ab6686d4a312c27ffff0f702e3644/cf440/terminal-without-powerline.png 148w,\n/static/895ab6686d4a312c27ffff0f702e3644/d2d38/terminal-without-powerline.png 295w,\n/static/895ab6686d4a312c27ffff0f702e3644/b9e4f/terminal-without-powerline.png 590w,\n/static/895ab6686d4a312c27ffff0f702e3644/70c4b/terminal-without-powerline.png 653w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Now with some awesome tricks you can change it too\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/19e56b843f78e3f7078d0e909c0e87c4/8d2b4/terminal-with-powerline.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 474px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 64.76793248945147%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Terminal with powerline\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/19e56b843f78e3f7078d0e909c0e87c4/8d2b4/terminal-with-powerline.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/19e56b843f78e3f7078d0e909c0e87c4/8ee9c/terminal-with-powerline.jpg 148w,\n/static/19e56b843f78e3f7078d0e909c0e87c4/ebbe7/terminal-with-powerline.jpg 295w,\n/static/19e56b843f78e3f7078d0e909c0e87c4/8d2b4/terminal-with-powerline.jpg 474w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>Step 1</h3>\n<p>Install <code class=\"language-text\">font-awesome</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">powerline</code>.\nFor Debian based operating system use the following command</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo apt install powerline fonts-powerline</code></pre></div>\n<p>This command might be different for different flavours of Linux based Operating system</p>\n<h3>Step 2</h3>\n<p>Change the configurations of your <code class=\"language-text\">.bashrc</code>.\nOpen the terminal and type <code class=\"language-text\">nano ~/.bashrc</code> or open your <code class=\"language-text\">.bashrc</code> in any text editor.\nAdd the following lines</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">if [ -f `which powerline-daemon` ]; then\n   powerline-daemon -q\n   POWERLINE_BASH_CONTINUATION=1\n   POWERLINE_BASH_SELECT=1\n   . /usr/share/powerline/bindings/bash/powerline.sh\nfi</code></pre></div>\n<p>Make sure the last line in the above is the path where the <code class=\"language-text\">powerline</code> tool is installed. It might be different for different operating system. Set this path according to your operating system.</p>\n<h3>Step 3</h3>\n<p>Source your <code class=\"language-text\">.bashrc</code> file in order to add changes.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">source ~/.bashrc</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Adding powerline to your Shell","date":"March 21, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/Powerline/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/PythonInteractiveCommandLine/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Invoking the command line with python"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/ConnectingToTor/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Connecting to Tor"}}}}}